The documents provide evidence that the film "Ray" was indeed produced by Stuart Benjamin. The relevant text from file_path: /Users/stefanomarchesin/Research/fshami/Rag/docs/dbpedia_2660/re-ranker-msmarco/71.txt is:

"The producing team behind “Ray” has set its sights on Broadway, acquiring rights from the Ray Charles Estate and Ray Charles Enterprises.

 Stuart Benjamin — who worked on “Ray” for 15 years before it opened last fall — will again partner with Howard and Karen Baldwin on the project, to be produced by Benjamin Prods.  and Baldwin Entertainment Group."

This text clearly indicates that Stuart Benjamin was a producer of the film "Ray".
